Two suspects have been arrested after they were allegedly found in possession of illegal firearms and rounds of ammunition at Sundumbili, in eMandeni on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast. Provincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele says police acted on an intelligence tip-off about the suspects who were allegedly on their way to commit a robbery in the area. “The team proceeded to Masamonco area in Sundumbili where a suspicious vehicle was spotted and searched, two occupants in the vehicle were both arrested and aged between 21 and 42.” “The suspects will also be profiled to check on whether they are not linked to other cases in Sundumbili and surrounding areas even in the province, as they are charged for possession of unlicensed of firearms and live ammunition,” added Mbhele. 